# Mirrorace Development Rules

## Project Overview

**mirrorace** is a Node.js CLI tool that acts as a smart proxy for npm registries. It runs a local HTTP proxy that races requests across multiple npm mirrors and selects the fastest responding mirror, with automatic fallback on failures. It rewrites tarball URLs to ensure lockfile portability.

- Repository: https://github.com/amirkabiri/mirrorace
- License: MIT
- Node.js: >= 18 (required)
- Package manager: pnpm@10.14.0 (strictly pinned)
- Build tool: esbuild (bundles to CommonJS)

