## Critical Algorithms

### Mirror Selection (stats.js)

Mirrors scored using EWMA (Exponentially Weighted Moving Average) of throughput:

- `score = throughputScore / (1 + failures * 5)`
- Throughput tracked in bytes/sec
- On success: `failures *= 0.85`
- On failure: `failures = failures * 0.6 + 1`
- Alpha for throughput EWMA: `0.4`

Winner determined by `stats.sorted(mirrors)`; fastest & most reliable wins.

### Metadata Race (metadata.js)

- Races ALL mirrors in parallel (Promise.allSettled style via custom `firstFulfilled`)
- First mirror with `response.ok` wins; losers aborted immediately
- Timeout: 8 seconds per mirror
- JSON response parsed; `dist.tarball` URLs rewritten to `https://registry.npmjs.org` canonical form
- Headers filtered to remove `host`, `content-length`, `connection`, `accept-encoding`

### Tarball Wave Race (tarball.js)

- Mirrors processed in waves of 3 (`RACE_PARALLELISM = 3`)
- Each wave races mirrors in parallel
- Winner is first mirror that starts streaming bytes (not just first response header)
- Winner piped to client via Node stream
- If stream fails (bytes already sent), connection destroyed; fallback to next wave
- Timeout: 30 seconds for first byte
- After success, throughput recorded to stats

### URL Rewriting (metadata.js)

- `rewriteTarballUrls()` recursively walks JSON
- `canonicalizeTarballUrl()` extracts tarball path and prefixes with `OFFICIAL_NPM_REGISTRY`
- Regex: `\/(?:@[^/]+\/)?[^/]+\/-\/[^/]+\.tgz$`
- Ensures lockfiles reference `registry.npmjs.org`, preserving portability

## Build & Test

**CRITICAL:** Use `pnpm` exclusively for all development tasks. Do not use `npm` or `yarn`.

```bash
# Install dependencies (always use pnpm)
pnpm install

# Build
pnpm run build    # esbuild ã dist/cli.cjs

# Test (MUST pass after every change)
pnpm test         # node --test test/*.test.js

# Release (CI/CD)
pnpm run release  # semantic-release
```

**Mandatory:** Run `pnpm test` after every code change and verify all tests pass before committing. Never commit code that breaks existing tests.

## Configuration

**Config file** (`-c <path>` or `--config`): YAML with either:

```yaml
mirrors:
  - https://registry.npmjs.org
  - https://registry.npmmirror.com
```

or plain array:

```yaml
- https://registry.npmmirror.com
- https://mirrors.cloud.tencent.com/npm
```

If no config provided, uses `DEFAULT_MIRRORS` from `mirrors.js` plus official npm registry appended automatically.

Official npm registry URL: `https://registry.npmjs.org` (constant `OFFICIAL_NPM_REGISTRY`).

## CLI Interface

```
mirrorace [-c <mirrors.yaml>] [--verbose] <pnpm|npm|yarn> [args...]
```

Supported package managers: npm, pnpm, yarn (strict Set check in `runner.js`).

All args after package manager name forwarded directly.

Environment variables set for package manager:
- `npm_config_registry`
- `NPM_CONFIG_REGISTRY`
- `YARN_NPM_REGISTRY_SERVER`
- `YARN_REGISTRY`

## Logging

Verbose mode (`--verbose`): logs to stderr with `[mirrorace]` prefix:
- `mirrors: <list>`
- `proxy listening on http://127.0.0.1:<port>`
- `metadata: winner=<mirror>`
- `tarball: winner=<mirror> delivered XB in Yms (ZK/s)`

## Error Handling

- Proxy errors: `500 { error: "internal proxy error" }`
- Method not allowed: `405` with `Allow: GET, HEAD`
- Not found: `404 { error: "not found" }`
- All mirrors failed (non-404): `502`
- All mirrors 404: `404` with descriptive message
- `x-mirrorace-mirror` header included on every successful response

## Performance Notes

- Metadata: 8s timeout; tarball: 30s timeout for first byte
- Tarball waves run 3 mirrors at a time to limit concurrent connections
- Throughput measured only if bytes sent & elapsed > 0; otherwise just recordSuccess
- `stats.recordThroughput()` uses EWMA to smooth performance over time

## Testing Patterns

- Fake registry (`test/helpers/fake-registry.js`): creates local HTTP server simulating npm registry
- Configurable: `delayMs`, `status`, `body`, `tarballBytes`, `notFoundFor`, `responseChunkDelayMs`
- Tests use Node's built-in `node:test` framework; no Jest/Mocha
- Each test cleans up proxy and fake registries in `finally` blocks
- Integration tests verify race conditions, fallback, URL rewriting

